---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import CTASection from "../components/CTASection.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="AP Dev Pro — Independent software engineering and cloud consulting by a hands-on engineer. Practical, experienced, trustworthy. AWS, serverless, TypeScript, Python, AI."
  ogUrl="https://apcloud.pro/about"
>
  <section class="pb-16 pt-24 sm:pb-20 sm:pt-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-electric-400">About</p>
        <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-5xl text-balance">
          Hands-on engineering,<br />no unnecessary complexity
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-20 sm:pb-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-5">
        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="lg:col-span-2">
          <div class="sticky top-28 space-y-6">
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy-900 p-5">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400">Focus Areas</h3>
              <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-electric-500/10 text-xs text-electric-400">⚡</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">AWS Serverless Architecture</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-cyan-500/10 text-xs text-cyan-400">🖥️</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">Full-Stack Development</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-violet-500/10 text-xs text-violet-400">🔄</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">Cloud Automation & DevOps</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded bg-emerald-500/10 text-xs text-emerald-400">🤖</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">AI & Agentic Workflows</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy-900 p-5">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400">Tech I Work With</h3>
              <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                {[
                  "AWS", "Lambda", "DynamoDB", "API Gateway", "AppSync",
                  "TypeScript", "Python", "React", "Node.js", ".NET",
                  "SQL Server", "PostgreSQL", "CDK", "Terraform", "Docker",
                  "GitHub Actions", "CloudFront", "S3", "Cognito", "Step Functions",
                ].map((tech) => (
                  <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-700 bg-navy-900 px-2.5 py-1 text-xs text-slate-400">
                    {tech}
                  </span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <!-- Bio -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-3 space-y-6 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="text-lg">
            I'm a software engineer and cloud consultant who helps businesses move quickly without overengineering. I've spent years building production systems across the stack — from .NET and SQL Server backends to serverless TypeScript and Python services on AWS.
          </p>

          <p>
            What sets me apart isn't a particular technology. It's the ability to look at a business problem, cut through the noise, and build exactly what's needed — nothing more, nothing less. I don't push technology for its own sake. I push for solutions that work, that are maintainable, and that make sense for the team that will own them.
          </p>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy-900 p-6">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-100">Why work with me</h2>
            <div class="mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-electric-400">Direct Access</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  You work directly with the person building your system. No account managers, no junior developers learning on your dime.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-electric-400">Pragmatic Approach</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  I choose the right tool for the job, not the trendy one. Serverless when it fits, containers when they're needed, monoliths when they make sense.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-electric-400">Knowledge Transfer</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  I document, explain, and walk your team through everything I build. The goal is for you to own your systems confidently.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-electric-400">Speed & Quality</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  Modern tooling — including AI-assisted development — lets me deliver high-quality work faster than traditional consulting shops.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            I work with startups shipping their first product, established businesses modernizing legacy systems, and technical teams that need an experienced pair of hands for a critical project. Every engagement starts with a conversation — no commitments, no pressure, just a honest discussion about what you're trying to achieve.
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-400">
            Based in the United States. Available for remote engagements worldwide.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Let's work together"
    description="Reach out to discuss your project, your challenges, or just to say hello. I respond to every message personally."
    ctaLabel="Get in Touch"
    ctaHref="/contact"
  />
</Layout>
